title: For Sale:  50bmg single shot with lots of extras
postcontent:
Up for sale is my .50bmg Vulcan rifle I have chambered and fired about 50 rounds through this gun without a hiccup from 5 degrees Fahrenheit to 98 degrees Fahrenheit.   This gun is sighted in at 400yds right now.  We started at 100yds then 200yds then 300yds then 400yds.  I have owned this gun for about 3 years and just don’t shoot it enough, last year I didn’t even get it out to shoot.  This year I have taken it out twice to get it from 200yds up to 400yds.  This gun shoots a pattern of about 3moa at 400yds, I just don’t have time to take it out to further distances and I recently lost my long distance range.  This gun is a great gun for the price I paid $1800.00 for the gun and $850.00 for the scope and another $385 for the case not including ammo.  The sale comes with the gun, scope, case, and about 50 rounds of ammunition.  I will send the empty brass I have along with the tips I bought to reload. Below is the info that came with the gun and the pics of the gun.


The V50SS rifle features a massive SAE 4150 receiver and a three lug bolt with a 60-degree bolt throw, cock on opening action, a shell holder type extractor for absolutely positive extraction. With a solid laminate wood stock. The barrel is machined from ordnance grade, chrome moly, high vanadium steel hardened to Rc 28-32. The barrel is 30” long, has 8 grooves, 1-15” right hand twist and features a SAAMI spec chamber which will allow the use of any SAAMI spec ammo. The barrel and all external steel parts, are manganese phosphate finished for long lasting good looks and corrosion protection. The V50SS utilizes the time proven standard, '98 Mauser trigger system for absolute safety. This rifle also features a high efficiency "shark fin" muzzle break, machined from solid bar stock and threaded on to the muzzle of the barrel with 1-12 TPI threads. This muzzle break is designed to reduce felt recoil to that of a 12 ga. Shotgun. The muzzle break can be “Tuned” to the barrel by altering the length via the long thread shank. This feature allows the operator to find the “sweet spot” for the break that gives the best accuracy. An M1913 Picatinny scope rail is attached via oversized grade 8 allen screws for easy mounting of optics. The oversized recoil shoulder distributes the recoil over a large surface area affording rock solid mounting to the stock. The bolt has three huge locking surfaces and a 60 degree throw. It features a “primary extraction” cam for positive extraction of the case. The receiver is machined from bar stock SAE 4150 steel and features pressure release vents for BOTH case separation and primer pierce, making this one of the strongest, safest actions available. We have tested these actions and bolts to pressures exceeding 100,000 psi with no evidence of failure. The wood laminate stock and rubber but pad absorb the recoil to further reduce felt recoil and allow the shooter to comfortably shoot all day.

 Scope, bipod and case are included for my asking price of $2500.00.  The scope is a SIII was $850.00 new and has only seen the 50 rounds of ammo shot through this rifle

The injection molded shell has incredible strength and rigidity and will provide the classic good looks and durability you demand in a holster. This shell is beyond tough.

Heavy Duty Belt Clips
The heavy duty belt clips are custom made, to our specs, by the same folks that originally developed them for John Bianchi and Neal Perkins in 1963. We think they are the best clips available in the world. Our belt clips are manufactured with the toughest spring steel available. Like everything else on our holsters, these are the best parts you can get. Fits belts up to 1.75 inches.

Steel Fasteners
The fasteners are made from 100% black oxide coated steel. Very strong. Very reliable. Some folks might say that our holsters are a little over-engineered. But we believe that the strength, durability and security of your holster is only as good as the components that hold it together.

Easy To Maintain
The Gunner Combat is designed to allow you to take your holster completely apart for periodic cleaning and waxing, and will ensure that your gun is protected as best as it can be.

Break Draw Feature
Break Draw allows you to bypass the holster's retention ramp and draw your Glock with virtually no resistance. This can be achieved by slightly rotating the butt of the gun towards the body during the draw. Break Draw allows for a very quiet draw (if necessary), makes drawing from a seated position very simple and also aids concealed carriers with a weaker arm strength in making a quick draw. Your Glock can also be drawn from the holster in the traditional manner.

Warranty
If the holster ever fails due to defects in materials or workmanship (not related to normal wear) we will repair or replace the holster, at our discretion, free of charge. You do not need to be the original owner to receive coverage.

Price: $67.99 + FREE Priority Shipping
